description.value: Mould-made pottery lamp with a double-convex body, a short round-topped splayed nozzle, and a raised circular base, flat below with a deep groove, and with an impressed letter alpha. The filling-hole is surrounded by two moulded rings, the outer one being surrounded by a horse-shoe of egg-and-tassel decoration in relief. Between the nozzle and the moulding is a scroll pattern. The shoulder is decorated with radiating grooves. There is a plain lug on the right side, and one in the form of a dolphin on the left. The top of the nozzle has a short transverse groove. Decorated with an orange-brown slip.

description.value: Mould-made pottery plastic lamp in the form of a lantern flanked by two erotes holding torches. Below each figure is a short semicircular nozzle, projecting from a deep plinth. On the front of the lantern in relief is a shrine of Aphrodite, or perhaps Athena, in the form of a gabled building supported by columns, containing a standing female figure in a long chiton, resting her left hand on a shield. The domed top of the lantern has a pierced lug. The back of the lamp has a large semicircular cut-out for fuel. The front is covered with a red slip.
